\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 ## Society of Unified Life (SOUL) \f1\endash  Core Role Structure & Operational Model\par
\par
### \f2\u-10180?\u-8435?\f1  \f0 Purpose\par
\par
SOUL is a decentralized, nonviolent, ethically grounded framework for individual and collective transformation. It provides a scalable model for community-based service, leadership development, and peaceful cooperation, with applications ranging from local neighborhood chapters to interplanetary governance.\par
\par
---\par
\par
### \f2\u-10179?\u-9023?\f1  \f0 Organizational Overview\par
\par
#### Local Chapters: **SOUL Nodes**\par
\par
* Grassroots groups formed by aligned individuals or families.\par
* Governed by a founding **Steward**, with rotating roles and open decision-making.\par
* Activities include service missions, skill-sharing, reflection circles, and civic outreach.\par
\par
#### Regional Coalitions: **SOUL Constellations**\par
\par
* Voluntary networks of neighboring SOUL Nodes that choose to collaborate.\par
* Coordinate regional events (e.g., cleanups, campouts, workshops).\par
* Share knowledge, resources, and mentorship across locations.\par
\par
#### Global Framework: **SOUL Nexus**\par
\par
* A decentralized, open-source platform of communication and coordination.\par
* Hosts the collective memory, infrastructure, training materials, and transparency tools.\par
* Exists to keep the SOUL framework alive across time and geography\f1\emdash even without central leadership.\par
\par
