### \f2\u-10179?\u-9028?\f1  \f0 Governance Summary\par
\par
SOUL chapters are encouraged to adopt governance models that reflect:\par
\par
* **Flat hierarchy** where possible\par
* **Transparency and accountability** always\par
* **Adaptability to scale** as the chapter grows\par
* **Checks and balances** to prevent stagnation or dominance\par
\par
#### \f2\u-10179?\u-8903?\f1  \f0 Key Roles (Flexible, but Anchored in Function)\par
\par
| Role            | Purpose                                            | Notes                                                                 |\par
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\par
| **Steward**     | Ethical anchor, keeps continuity & mission aligned | May initially also act as Facilitator/Coordinator in small chapters   |\par
| **Facilitator** | Runs meetings and holds space                      | Should rotate\f1\emdash can be selected by rotation, volunteering, or soft vote |\par
| **Coordinator** | Leads missions or events                           | Appointed per mission; confirmed by chapter vote                      |\par
| **Chairperson** | Point person for compliance or finances            | Required if handling legal filings or funds; not a leadership role    |\par
| **Council**     | Optional group for chapter oversight and support   | Helps resolve tension and guide structure if roles rotate out         |\par
\par
#### \f3\u-10180?\u-8848?\u-497?\f1  \f0 Voting & Authority Guidelines\par
\par
* **New Stewards** must be **elected by a full chapter vote**, not appointed by the Council.\par
* **Coordinators** may be proposed by anyone but should be **confirmed by chapter consensus or soft vote**.\par
* **Facilitators** may be:\par
\par
  * Drawn from a volunteer list\par
  * Rotated randomly or alphabetically\par
  * Selected from within the Council (if one exists)\par
* **Council members** can be:\par
\par
  * Volunteers approved by chapter consensus\par
  * Elected through a chapter-wide vote\par
  * Automatically included if they currently serve as Steward, Facilitator, or Coordinator\par
  * Selected by completion of certain role paths (e.g., Mentors or Pathbearers)\par
\par
#### \f2\u-10179?\u-8956?\f1  \f0 Stepping In (Especially for Small or New Chapters)\par
\par
When a chapter is just beginning:\par
\par
* The **Steward may temporarily act as Facilitator, Coordinator, and Chairperson** until others are ready to participate.\par
* As the group grows, these duties **should be shared and rotated**, and formal processes introduced.\par
* A **Council** may emerge organically or by vote\f1\emdash helping ensure direction and ethical alignment without creating hierarchy.\par
\par
#### \f3\u-10179?\u-8479?\u-497?\f1  \f0 Built-In Safeguards\par
\par
| Check or Balance                | Purpose                                        |\par
| ------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |\par
| Steward veto (used sparingly)   | Prevents unethical or misaligned decisions     |\par
| Full chapter vote for key roles | Ensures democratic legitimacy                  |\par
| Public meeting notes & finances | Builds trust and transparency                  |\par
| Council term limits (optional)  | Prevents stagnation or unearned authority      |\par
| Open role paths & skill-sharing | Encourages new members to step into leadership |\par
\par
